&lt;p&gt;Saturday morning, shop lights humming, a fresh cup of coffee cooling beside a maple tabletop you’ve been saving for months. You click on the extractor, roll the hose into your elbow, and set the 5&amp;quot; sander on the surface. The pad spins up with that familiar soft whir. You start at the far corner, let the tool’s own weight settle, and begin to track across the grain. Two passes in, you see it: faint pigtails reflecting in the raking light. You aren’t new to sanding; you’re careful with grits, dust removal, and vacuum airflow. But random orbital sanding still has a way of punishing rushed technique. You realize your grip has tightened and your forearm is leaning into the head—too much pressure. The speed dial is still at max from the last adhesive removal task. Heat builds, the abrasive dulls, and the swirl gremlins come to life.&lt;/p&gt;</summary><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/images/brand/17.webp" medium="image"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/30/proper-hand-pressure-and-speed-control-random-orbital-sanding/cards/facebook/proper-hand-pressure-and-speed-control-random-orbital-sanding.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/30/proper-hand-pressure-and-speed-control-random-orbital-sanding/cards/facebook/proper-hand-pressure-and-speed-control-random-orbital-sanding.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/30/proper-hand-pressure-and-speed-control-random-orbital-sanding/cards/facebook/proper-hand-pressure-and-speed-control-random-orbital-sanding.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/30/proper-hand-pressure-and-speed-control-random-orbital-sanding/cards/instagram/proper-hand-pressure-and-speed-control-random-orbital-sanding.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/30/proper-hand-pressure-and-speed-control-random-orbital-sanding/cards/instagram/proper-hand-pressure-and